{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d9540aba-0b90-4410-b7ff-be6fb8b07dcb","content":"The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them. For **analyzing** a `.dmp` file, here are your best options:\n\n### Tools for Crash Dump Analysis\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform)\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze <path-to-dump.dmp>\n   ```\n   Then use commands like `clrstack`, `pe` (print exception), `dumpheap`, `threads`.\n\n2. **Visual Studio** (Windows) — Open the `.dmp` file directly; it provides a rich GUI for managed debugging.\n\n3. **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS)\n   ```bash\n   dotnet-sos install\n   lldb --core <dump-file>\n   ```\n\n### Quick Triage Commands (in `dotnet-dump analyze`)\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `pe` | Print last exception |\n| `threads` | List all threads |\n| `clrstack` | Stack trace of current thread |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n| `gcroot <addr>` | Find what's keeping an object alive |\n\nWould you like me to help you run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file if it's accessible in this environment?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"86072d28-8079-4004-9624-41a1865c8b7f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description specifically says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is NOT appropriate here since the user wants to analyze a dump, not collect one.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":458},"id":"05dab980-2552-4762-8351-15c92b4645ce","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:08:43.881Z","parentId":"4bc54aaa-cda8-4c37-bc2e-a4fe764d5729"}
